song_name: In The Middle Of The Night

version_description: Slightly more accurate chords in verse.

This tab includes all parts of the song, including the instrumental, and contains every part that is in the original song (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O5qS8MLUUzI). In the very last chorus, remember to use ritardando on the final D and C/E.

More accurate chord version of this fabolous song was still missing, taking into consideration it could be played both picking and strumming. Based upon combined insights of the original version Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vmezIIrFQmY) and the cover of Jasper Steverlinck Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QIKuch74pBs. Attempt to find balance between nuancated version still playable while singing. Chord names are based on Chord Finder subtool in GuitarPro 6. If played strumming beter replace the G6(no5) by Em/G, i.e. instead of trying to omit the 5th string, play the si on 2nd fret.

This version contains every chord in the song and breaks down some sections to see which chords are contained in a held part of the singing. One of the instrumentals is quite short, and it is only there because there is a small piano break between chorus and verse.
Added some non-root note bass to the chords.
Couldn't find a version so The Bed and Breakfast Men helped me with the chords. With out them this wouldnt have happen thanks.
